                ounces when you select the US unit system. You can switch units
                at any time; just recalculate to update the display.
              </p>

              <h3>Does this calculator handle dual-lye recipes?</h3>
              <p>
                At the moment, this tool assumes a single lye type per batch
                (either NaOH or KOH). For advanced dual-lye recipes (e.g. 60%
                KOH / 40% NaOH for cream soap), you can run two separate
                calculations and combine the lye amounts manually.
              </p>

              <h3>How accurate are the results?</h3>
              <p>
                The formulas and SAP values are consistent with what experienced
                soap makers use. The main sources of error in real life are
                inaccurate scales, mis-typed numbers, and variations in oil
                composition. Always double-check your inputs and consider
                running a small test batch when trying a new recipe.
              </p>

              <h3>Can I use this for hot process soap?</h3>
              <p>
                Yes. The lye and water calculations are the same for cold and
                hot process. For hot process, many makers use slightly lower
                water or higher lye concentration to speed up cook time, but the
                underlying math is identical.
